To determine the angle in the right triangle shown in the diagram, we can use the tangent function. The triangle has legs of lengths 4 and 8. According to the Pythagorean theorem, the hypotenuse \( c \) is calculated as follows:

\[
\begin{array}{r l r}
4^{2} + 8^{2} = c^{2} & 16 + 64 = c^{2} & 80 = c^{2} \\
\sqrt{80} = c & 8.94 \approx c
\end{array}
\]

Next, we use the tangent function to find the angle \( \Theta \):

\[
\begin{array}{r l r}
\tan \Theta = \frac{\text{opposite}}{\text{adjacent}} & \tan \Theta = \frac{4}{8} & \tan \Theta = \frac{1}{2} \\
\Theta = \tan^{-1}\left(\frac{1}{2}\right) & \Theta \approx 26.57^{\circ}
\end{array}
\]

![The angle at the green arrow is approximately 26.57 degrees](image4)

Therefore, the angle in the right triangle is approximately \( 26.57^\circ \).
